    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="779"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d779">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115/6178</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 1, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received December 2, 8.15 a.
                        m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3323. Your 2476, November 19. Foreign Office inform me in reply to my further
                    representations that British Government still in communication with French
                    Government regarding matter of exportation of German and Austrian hops to United
                    States and that decision reached will be communicated to me without delay. I am
                    giving this matter my personal attention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
